text: Dihydrolanosterol, or 24,25-Dihydrolanosterol, also called Lanostenol, is a sterol and the C24-25 hydrogenated products of lanosterol, dihydrolanosterol can be demethylated by mammal or yeast cytochrome P450 sterol 14alpha- demethylase. ==See also== * Lanosterol * Obtusifoliol * Cycloartenol ==References== Category:sterols
title: Dihydrolanosterol
